{title: Sugarfoot Rag}
{artist: Porter Wagoner}
{composer: Recorded by Porter Wagoner written by Hank Garland}

[G]Gonna get out my sycamore and [F]shine up my shoes
[G]Meet my baby and [D7]tell her the [G]news
I bet my bundle on a [F]swayback nag
And I [G]came home winner with a [D7]plenty o'[G]swag
One foot two foot slew foot drag
Swing your honey to the [D7]Sugarfoot [G]Rag
Dig a little jig with a zig and a zag
And listen to the guitar play the [D7]Sugarfoot [G]Rag
Got a big jug o'cider and a [F]bottle of wine
[G]One for my honey and the [D7]other'n is [G]mine
Sip on the cider and sip [F]on the wine
We [G]both sip together and a [D7]have a good [G]time
Repeat #2
Gonna spend all my money and a [F]git on a jag
[G]Swing my honey to the [D7]Sugarfoot [G]Rag
Walk right up and [F]stomp on the floor
And [G]swing up the middle with a [D7]shoofly [G]four
Repeat #2